[base]
# valkey-bench-rs
Rust high-performance benchmarking framework for Valkey/Redis vector search.
Measures latency (p50/p99), throughput (QPS), and recall across HNSW configs.
Architecture: src/runner/ (execution engine), src/dataset/ (generation + ground truth), src/metrics/ (histograms + export).
Build: cargo build --release. Test: cargo test. Bench: cargo bench.
Feature flags: --features neon, --features sve, --features avx2.
Conventions: thiserror+anyhow, tokio async, clap derive, no unwrap in lib code.

[debug]
Connection pool timeout: check Valkey server reachability.
SIMD dispatch: wrong feature flag causes silent scalar fallback.
Ground truth mismatch: regenerate if index params changed.
OOM on large datasets: check --max-vectors and system memory.
Use RUST_LOG=debug for trace output.

[docs]
Audience: contributors and users evaluating vector search performance.
Results format in docs/results-format.md. Diagrams in Mermaid.

[review]
No unwrap() — use ? or expect() with context.
No blocking IO in async. CLI flags need help text + README.
Benchmark configs must be reproducible (fixed seeds).

[command:_always:status]
Show project health: cargo check, cargo test --no-run, valkey-cli ping.

[command:debug:profile]
Profile benchmark from $ARGUMENTS: perf record + cargo flamegraph, analyze hot paths.

[command:debug:repro-recall]
Reproduce recall issue from $ARGUMENTS: check seed, verify ground truth, single-query verbose.

[command:docs:gen-bench-report]
Generate benchmark report: parse results/, comparison tables, latency charts in Mermaid.

[command:review:check-simd]
Review SIMD changes: verify scalar fallback, feature flags, ARM/x86 parity, criterion before/after.

[agent:_always:planner]
Planning agent. Break tasks into steps. Suggest benchmarks for any perf-critical change.

[agent:debug:perf-investigator]
Performance specialist. Measure first, hypothesize, instrument, validate. Use flamegraph and criterion.

[agent:review:rust-reviewer]
Rust reviewer. Check ownership, error handling, unsafe, async correctness, SIMD safety, reproducibility.

[skill:debug:flamegraph]
# Flamegraph
Build with frame pointers, perf record, inferno-collapse-perf, inferno-flamegraph.
Look for hot paths in distance computation and HNSW traversal.

[skill:docs:results-visualizer]
# Results Visualization
Parse CSV, generate Mermaid charts: latency distributions, throughput, recall vs speed.

[mcp:_always:github]
{"type": "http", "url": "https://api.githubcopilot.com/mcp/"}

[mcp:debug:valkey-server]
{"command": "valkey-cli", "args": ["ping"]}

[hook:_always:PreToolUse]
[{"matcher": "Bash", "hooks": [{"type": "command", "command": ".claude/hooks/block-rm.sh"}]}]

[hook:debug:Stop]
[{"hooks": [{"type": "agent", "prompt": "Run cargo test and confirm all tests pass", "timeout": 120}]}]

[lsp:_always:rust-analyzer]
{"command": "rust-analyzer", "args": [], "extensionToLanguage": {".rs": "rust"}}

[memory:debug]
SimSIMD dispatch refactored — check src/metrics/distance.rs for dispatch table.
ARM Graviton3 needs sve, Graviton2 uses neon only.

[inherit]
recursive: skills
